main event: A military source observed a bright, highly illuminated object at an altitude of 10 to 15,000 feet in Honolulu on January 16, 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3 minutes and had no visible structure., It appeared to have aerodynamic features., The object was described as being oval in shape and luminous., The object could not be tracked on radar and did not resemble any known aircraft., The conclusion drawn was that it was probably an aircraft.
